tspan.tspan: D. CAMERON LEMMON
In the four years I’ve worked at SparkFun, I’ve been privileged to
get to know my awesome coworkers around the company and
the members of SWIT very well. These people, and how they come
together every day, are a big part of what makes the SparkFun
experience special. As a team, we each have our strengths, our
specific talents, that help each project we tackle be a success in
supporting the goals of SparkFun. It is my familiarity with this team
that has me excited for the opportunity to lead us in continuing to
operate at our best level.
Having started as a developer and then moving into my current
role of sysadmin, I’ve had the unique experience of working on
both sides of SWIT, gaining in depth knowledge of our applications,
architectures, and methods; as well as how they have evolved
and ideas for continued growth we’d like to make. This
knowledge lets me start from day one to support our daily business
needs, while continuing to move forward with our transition plans,
and prepare for what comes next.
At the beginning of my career, I managed construction projects,
moving them from ideas on paper into physical installations. From
there, I transitioned into teaching, where I was responsible for
mentoring, guiding, and teaching a full classroom. At SparkFun, I
realized I wanted to know more, and learn the skills needed to
better understand the business. I wanted to move away from
being an individual contributor, so decided to go back to school. I
was able to complete my MBA this spring, and am excited for the
opportunity to implement ideas I’ve gained about fostering the
best work from the best people.
Thank you for your consideration,
